<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="215" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,153,755]" pageId="14" pageNumber="215">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,328,656,683]" pageId="14" pageNumber="215">Comments</emphasis>
. This species is related to both 
<taxonomicName box="[675,803,657,683]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Phytomia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="215" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aurigera">
<emphasis box="[675,692,658,683]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="215">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[705,803,658,683]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="215">aurigera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[855,961,657,683]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Megaspis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="215" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bullata">
<emphasis box="[855,961,657,683]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="215">P. bullata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but differs in the presence of a clear protuberance on the distal part of the hind femur, and the paler coloration of face and legs. It is only known from a small series collected at the 
<typeStatus box="[398,446,729,755]" pageId="14" pageNumber="215">type</typeStatus>
locality.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
